==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Periwig
<hw>Per"i*wig</hw> <pr>(p⟦ecr⟧r"⟦icr⟧*w⟦icr⟧g)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[OE. <ets>perrwige</ets>, <ets>perwicke</ets>, corrupt. fr. F.
<ets>perruque</ets>; cf. OD. <ets>peruyk</ets>, from French. See
<er>Peruke</er>, and cf. <er>Wig</er>.]</ety> <def>A headdress of false
hair, usually covering the whole head, and representing the natural
hair; a wig.</def> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Periwig</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Periwig
